# Shell scripts are executed on Linux (deploy target + cron) via their
# shebang line. A Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true silently converts
# them to CRLF, which breaks `/usr/bin/env bash` (looks for an interpreter
# literally named "bash\r") and `set -o pipefail` parsing — this bit a real
# production deploy once. Force LF regardless of the checking-out platform.
*.sh text eol=lf
